Coloration variable, generally dusky gray or tan background with light black mottling, occasionally with reddish or burgundy coloration on opisthosoma. Carapace coloration variable, from prominent longitudinal black stripe on carapace flanks to series of three or four black wedges or no pattern at all. Spermathecae frequently asymmetrical (
Figs. 57, 59
), with one positioned ventral to cd and visible through the ventral integument, other positioned dorsal to cd.
